Title : Bernardo Hees
Text : {{short description|Bazillian businessman}}
{{portuguese name|Vieira|Hees}}
{{BLP refimprove|date=October 2015}}
'''Bernardo Vieira Hees''' is a Brazilian economist and businessman. He held the position of [[chief executive officer]] (CEO) of [[The Kraft Heinz Company]] until stepping down on June 30, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hirsch |first1=Lauren |title=Kraft Heinz CEO Bernardo Hees to step down, will be replaced by AB InBevâ€™s Miguel Patricio |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/04/22/kraft-heinz-taps-new-ceo-ab-inbevs-miguel-patricio.html |website=CNBC |publisher=NBCUniversal Media, LLC |accessdate=22 April 2019}}</ref> He previously served as CEO of [[The H.J. Heinz Company]], [[Burger King Corporation]], and [[America Latina Logistica]], Latin America's largest railroad and logistics company. Hees is also a partner in the global investment firm [[3G Capital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=20608798&ticker=BKW |title=Executive Compensation & Stock Trading - Businessweek |publisher=Investing.businessweek.com |date=2015-09-30 |accessdate=2015-10-24}}</ref><ref>[http://news.heinz.com/press-release/finance/bernardo-hees-be-appointed-chief-executive-officer-hj-heinz-company-following] {{dead link|date=October 2015}}</ref>

He holds a BA in [[Economics]] from the [[Pontifical Catholic University of Rio de Janeiro]], and an MBA from [[Warwick Business School]] in the [[United Kingdom]].

